cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with radio resource scheduling in a vehicle-to-vehicle communication network. 
2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also likely as the paper models the interactions among VUE-pairs as a stochastic game. 
3. cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the optimization of expected long-term performance. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with the regulation of frequency allocation by the RSU. 
5. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is relevant as the paper deals with the interactions among multiple VUE-pairs.
